strategy.description:
LATTICE CONFIGURATION PREDICTION STRATEGY
==========================================

This strategy generates the 10-20 most likely metal sublattice configurations
for a given N (number of unique metal positions).

The strategy combines:
1. Empirical patterns from 1802 AFLOW structures
2. Lattice-type-specific filling rules
3. N-decomposition into (in-plane) × (z-layers)
4. Special position preferences

PRIORITY ORDER:
1. Observed high-frequency patterns for this N
2. Lattice-specific templates at common special positions
3. Generated patterns from N-decomposition rules

Cubic-P.key_insight: BCC-like (1/2,1/2,1/2) at N=2, FCC face-centers at N=3-4

Cubic-F.key_insight: Diamond positions (1/4,1/4,1/4) appear early at N=2-3

Hexagonal-P.key_insight: Two competing N=2 patterns: z-doubled vs wurtzite-like

Tetragonal-I.key_insight: Body-centering shifts preferred z from 1/2 to 1/4
